{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":14054,"record_hash":"sha256:06de0ec506652e130f0e5c4cc72827854f30dd75893bb3a4f85afe2f37a72e96","timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:33:50.254Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Delete File: [REDACTED:entropy].md\n*** Add File: [REDACTED:entropy].md\n+# First POC Implementation Contract\n+\n+This is the implementation contract for the first Agent Session Capture POC.\n+When this page conflicts with broader architecture or future-work notes, this\n+page wins for the first implementation.\n+\n+## Goal\n+\n+Build the smallest safe proof that GitButler can capture agent log metadata from\n+an explicit Codex or Claude transcript path and write redacted session data into\n+GitMeta.\n+\n+The first patch should prove:\n+\n+- GitButler CLI can invoke capture behind a hidden feature-gated command.\n+- A new crate can parse Codex and Claude JSONL transcripts from an explicit path.\n+- Capture writes shareable-ready GitButler session data under `gitbutler:*`.\n+- Transcript envelopes are always captured, redacted, and deduplicated.\n+- Repeated capture is idempotent.\n+\n+## Implement Only This\n+\n+- New crate: `crates/but-agentlog` (`but_agentlog` in Rust code).\n+- Hidden CLI command behind feature flag `agentlog`:\n+\n+```text\n+but agentlog capture \\\n+  --agent codex \\\n+  --transcript-path <path> \\\n+  [--target project]\n+```\n+\n+- `codex` and `claude` are the supported agents in the first implementation.\n+- Keep agent handling closed and explicit. Codex and Claude should force a small\n+  shared parser/output boundary, not a plugin framework.\n+- `--transcript-path` is required.\n+- Default target is `project`.\n+- GitMeta writes use shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys.\n+- The command does not serialize, push, fetch, or sync GitMeta.\n+\n+## Do Not Implement Yet\n+\n+- No Cursor support.\n+- No background watcher.\n+- No session discovery.\n+- No `CODEX_THREAD_ID` lookup.\n+- No recent-file heuristics.\n+- No branch inference.\n+- No commit inference from `HEAD`.\n+- No GitMeta push/fetch/sync/serialization.\n+- No UI surface.\n+- No dependency on `but-api`, `but-db`, `but-ctx`, `but-claude`, `but-cursor`,\n+  or legacy virtual branch APIs.\n+- No branch/PR/commit association keys.\n+\n+## Dependency Decision\n+\n+Use the GitMeta GitHub repository pinned to an explicit revision:\n+\n+```toml\n+git-meta-lib = { git = \"https://github.com/git-meta/git-meta.git\", rev = \"[REDACTED:entropy]\" }\n+```\n+\n+Do not use a local path dependency for the POC, and do not float the dependency\n+on a branch. When updating GitMeta intentionally, replace the pinned revision\n+with the desired upstream commit.\n+\n+## CLI Contract\n+\n+```text\n+but agentlog capture --agent <codex|claude> --transcript-path <path>\n+```\n+\n+| Option                             | POC behavior                                                                                  |\n+| ---------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n+| `--agent codex` / `--agent claude` | Required. Other values fail as unsupported.                                                   |\n+| `--transcript-path <path>`         | Required. Must point to a readable JSONL transcript for the selected agent.                    |\n+| `--target <target>`                | Optional. Defaults to `project`. Pass explicit target strings to `Target::parse` without inference. |\n+\n+Default human/shell output is a single terse line. JSON output is the same\n+message in an object so hooks do not need to parse prose:\n+\n+```text\n+Captured 42 metadata records and 42 transcript records for project\n+```\n+\n+```json\n+{\n+\t\"message\": \"Captured 42 metadata records and 42 transcript records for project\"\n+}\n+```\n+\n+Normal human output, JSON output, and validation errors should not include full\n+transcript paths.\n+\n+## Agent Transcript Parsing\n+\n+POC parser reads JSONL line by line from one byte snapshot. Empty lines are\n+ignored. A malformed final non-empty line is treated as a partial write and\n+skipped; a malformed earlier line fails.\n+\n+Record indexes are 0-based over non-empty JSONL records. `last-record-index` is\n+the highest successfully parsed/captured source record index and never advances\n+for a skipped partial final line.\n+\n+### Codex\n+\n+Expected Codex record types observed so far:\n+\n+```text\n+session_meta\n+turn_context\n+response_item\n+event_msg\n+compacted\n+```\n+\n+Useful fields:\n+\n+| Field        | Codex source                                            | If missing                                 |\n+| ------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |\n+| session id   | `session_meta.payload.id` or payload session id         | derive session key from source path hash   |\n+| cwd          | `session_meta.payload.cwd` / `turn_context.payload.cwd` | continue if missing; validate when present |\n+| provider     | `session_meta.payload.model_provider`                   | omit scalar key                            |\n+| model        | `turn_context.payload.model` or model metadata          | omit scalar key                            |\n+| tool/version | `session_meta.payload.cli_version`                      | omit scalar key                            |\n+| event kind   | top-level `type` plus `payload.type` when present       | store top-level `type` only                |\n+| role         | `response_item.payload.role` for message records        | omit                                       |\n+| content text | obvious payload content/text/message fields             | omit                                       |\n+| tool name    | obvious payload tool/name fields                        | omit                                       |\n+| timestamp    | top-level `timestamp`                                   | omit from envelope                         |\n+\n+### Claude\n+\n+Claude Code stores local session transcripts as JSONL under\n+`~/.claude/projects/<encoded-cwd>/<session-id>.jsonl`, and `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR`\n+can move that config root. The POC still requires an explicit\n+`--transcript-path`; discovery is documented as future work in\n+[Capture Workflow](capture-workflow.md).\n+\n+Useful fields:\n+\n+| Field        | Claude source                                                     | If missing                                 |\n+| ------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |\n+| session id   | top-level `sessionId`                                             | derive session key from source path hash   |\n+| cwd          | top-level `cwd`                                                   | continue if missing; validate when present |\n+| provider     | fixed `anthropic` for Claude parser output                        | omit only if this changes later            |\n+| model        | `message.model` on assistant records                              | omit scalar key                            |\n+| tool/version | top-level `version`                                               | omit scalar key                            |\n+| event kind   | top-level `type` plus `message.type` when present                 | store top-level `type` only                |\n+| role         | `message.role`, falling back to top-level `user`/`assistant` type | omit                                       |\n+| content text | `message.content` string or text blocks                           | omit                                       |\n+| tool name    | obvious message tool/name fields                                  | omit                                       |\n+| timestamp    | top-level `timestamp`                                             | omit from envelope                         |\n+\n+If a transcript `cwd` exists, canonicalize it and accept it only when it is the\n+repo root or inside the repo worktree. Otherwise fail rather than guess. The POC\n+validates cwd but does not store cwd.\n+\n+## Storage Shape\n+\n+Use the `project` GitMeta target by default.\n+\n+Session index:\n+\n+```text\n+gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n+```\n+\n+Durable session prefix:\n+\n+```text\n+gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*\n+```\n+\n+Session-level keys:\n+\n+```text\n+:schema = gitbutler.agent-session.v1\n+:updated-at = <capture timestamp>\n+:sources = set<source-key>\n+:record-hashes = set<sha256:record>\n+:transcript = list<TranscriptEnvelope JSON>\n+```\n+\n+Source-level keys:\n+\n+```text\n+:source:<source-key>:agent\n+:source:<source-key>:provider\n+:source:<source-key>:model\n+:source:<source-key>:tool-version\n+:source:<source-key>:provider-session-key\n+:source:<source-key>:source-name\n+:source:<source-key>:source-size\n+:source:<source-key>:source-sha256\n+:source:<source-key>:last-record-index\n+:source:<source-key>:captured-at\n+```\n+\n+Do not store full transcript paths, cwd, git branch, or raw provider session ids.\n+`source-name` is basename only. `provider-session-key` is hashed.\n+\n+## Session and Source Keys\n+\n+Derive `session-key` deterministically:\n+\n+```text\n+sha256(agent + NUL + provider-session-id)\n+```\n+\n+If no provider session id exists:\n+\n+```text\n+sha256(agent + NUL + canonical-transcript-path-bytes)\n+```\n+\n+Derive `source-key` from the agent plus canonical transcript path bytes so a\n+durable session can later contain multiple source entries without metadata\n+collisions.\n+\n+## Transcript Envelope\n+\n+Append one redacted JSON object string per captured record:\n+\n+```json\n+{\n+\t\"schema\": \"gitbutler.agent-transcript.v1\",\n+\t\"source_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n+\t\"record_index\": 0,\n+\t\"record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n+\t\"timestamp\": \"...\",\n+\t\"event_kind\": \"...\",\n+\t\"event_category\": \"message\",\n+\t\"role\": \"user\",\n+\t\"content_text\": \"redacted normalized text when easy to extract\",\n+\t\"tool_name\": null,\n+\t\"source_record\": {}\n+}\n+```\n+\n+`content_text` is the normalized conversation message body when obvious to\n+extract. `event_category` is `session`, `context`, `message`, `tool`, or\n+`other`.\n+\n+Omit repeated session/source metadata from envelopes. Also omit cwd, git branch,\n+provider session ids, message ids, parent ids, turn ids, and redaction counters\n+from top-level envelope fields. Keep redacted `source_record` for provenance and\n+future normalization improvements.\n+\n+## Deduplication\n+\n+Stable record hash:\n+\n+```text\n+sha256(trimmed raw JSONL line bytes)\n+```\n+\n+Hash before envelope wrapping. Do not include capture timestamp, source path, or\n+record index in the hash.\n+\n+Important idempotency rule: metadata dedupe uses session-level `record-hashes`,\n+while transcript append dedupe is rebuilt from the stored transcript envelope\n+list. This keeps transcript appends idempotent and allows backfill if the\n+transcript list is missing while record hashes remain.\n+\n+For each record:\n+\n+1. Trim trailing newline/whitespace from the raw JSONL line.\n+2. Parse as JSON.\n+3. Compute `sha256` of the trimmed raw bytes.\n+4. Add the hash to `record-hashes` only if missing from existing/planned hashes.\n+5. Append an envelope only if `record_hash` is missing from existing/planned\n+   transcript envelopes.\n+\n+Source provenance keys should still update once per successful capture, even if\n+all records dedupe.\n+\n+## Privacy Rules\n+\n+| Data                          | POC default                                                             |\n+| ----------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n+| Transcript file discovery     | Never; explicit path only                                               |\n+| Transcript envelope records   | Always stored as redacted envelopes under `gitbutler:*`                 |\n+| Source path                   | Never stored; `source-name` is basename only                            |\n+| CWD                           | Validation-only, not stored                                             |\n+| Git branch                    | Not stored                                                              |\n+| Agent auth/config/cache files | Never read                                                              |\n+| [REDACTED:entropy] | Not implemented in first POC                                            |\n+\n+All stored agentlog values copied from transcripts are redacted before writing.\n+The POC does not store raw provider session ids.\n+\n+## Future Associations\n+\n+Do not implement branch, PR, change, or commit associations in this POC. Later,\n+when GitButler has an explicit target, write relationship references like:\n+\n+```text\n+<branch/change/commit target>\n+  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n+```\n+\n+The durable session remains project-scoped. See\n+[Future Use Cases](future-use-cases.md).\n+\n+## Acceptance Tests\n+\n+Minimum tests before calling the POC done:\n+\n+- `cargo test -p but-agentlog` passes.\n+- Parses Codex and Claude fixture JSONL from explicit paths.\n+- Missing transcript path fails clearly.\n+- Unsupported agent fails clearly.\n+- Default capture writes `gitbutler:agent-sessions` and\n+  `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*`.\n+- No `meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:*` keys are written for main session\n+  data.\n+- Source metadata uses basename-only `source-name`.\n+- Transcript envelopes contain only the slim per-record fields.\n+- Envelope `source_key` joins to source metadata.\n+- Running capture twice on the same fixture captures `N` then `0` new metadata\n+  records and appends transcript envelopes only once.\n+- Growing the fixture captures only new records.\n+- Missing transcript list backfills from stored envelopes and record hashes.\n+- Malformed final non-empty line is tolerated as partial write.\n+- Malformed middle line fails.\n+- Mismatched transcript `cwd` fails.\n+- Session ids are converted to hashed safe session keys.\n+- Human and JSON output do not contain the full transcript path.\n+\n+## Done Means\n+\n+The first POC is done when:\n+\n+- The command exists but is hidden and feature-gated.\n+- The new crate has focused unit/integration tests.\n+- GitButler builds with the feature enabled.\n+- Capture can be run against a fixture or real Codex/Claude transcript.\n+- Repeated capture is idempotent.\n+- No future-work behavior accidentally lands in the first patch.\n+\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:33:50.254Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}